Package: RTrace
Title: Architecture Governance and Static Analysis for R Projects
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("RTrace", "Contributors", , "maintainers@rtrace.dev", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: A static analysis and architecture governance platform for R
    projects and packages. RTrace scans R codebases for structural and
    architectural problems that style checkers and linters do not address,
    including layer/dependency-direction violations, circular module
    dependencies, project structure conventions, complexity hotspots, and
    common anti-patterns ('<<-', 'assign()', 'setwd()', hardcoded paths).
    Rules are declared in a versioned YAML configuration file and evaluated
    by an extensible rule engine, producing diagnostics that can be rendered
    as colored console output, 'JSON', 'Markdown', 'HTML', 'CSV', 'XML', or
    'SARIF' for use in interactive development and continuous integration.
